** Based in Murarrie, Queensland **

** Primary Purpose of Role **

  * To administer, support and maintain the Pathology technology enterprise and associated infrastructure services across the Pathology group multiple locations (i.e., local lab network infrastructure, security, physical and virtual servers, backup systems) 
  * Supporting and maintaining organizational computer systems, desktops, mobile phones and other peripherals. 
  * Responsible for the efficient and timely resolution of technology issues and maintenance, both on demand and per request 
  * Fulfilment and deployment of new or replacement hardware components, desktop and technology hardware and software components 
  * To ensure technology services tasks are managed effectively and responsibly, to agreed service 
  * Act as technical lead on Pathology IT project implementations 
  * Review, maintain and update IT processes and systems 

** To be considered for this role your skills and attributes should include: **

  * 2-5 years of experience in level 1 &/or 2 support roles 
  * Relevant qualification in IT or comparable experience - Microsoft, VMWare 
  * Ability to present and communicate both business and technical concepts. 
  * Strong customer service and technical skills 
  * Flexibility to work on-call outside of business hours on a challenging roster 
  * Exceptional written and verbal communication skills 
  * ITIL Foundation Certification is desirable 

** Employee benefits and wellbeing **

  * Access to a marketplace of exclusive discounts and vouchers from leading Australian and online retailers. 
  * An e-learning platform with access to a library of courses and learning paths. 
  * An Employee Assistance Program dedicated to employee health and wellbeing provided by professional coaches. 
  * Corporate health insurance discounts, banking benefits and novated leasing consultations. 

** Vaccination requirements **

As per the Healius Group Vaccination Policy, there may be some vaccination
requirements in some Hospital settings.

